    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "### Problem\n\nThere are a number of invisible unicode characters, including but not limited to:\r\n\r\n- Em Space: U+2003\r\n- Tag Space: U+E0020\r\n- Thin Space: U+2009\r\n- En Space: U+2002\r\n- Hair Space: U+200A\r\n- Zero Width No-Break Space: U+FEFF\r\n- Figure Space: U+2007\r\n- Punctuation Space: U+2008\r\n- Narrow No-Break Space: U+202F\r\n- Six-Per-Em Space: U+2006\r\n- Four-Per-Em Space: U+2005\r\n- Three-Per-Em Space: U+2004\r\n- Ideographic Space: U+3000\r\n- Medium Mathematical Space: U+205F\r\n\r\nThese characters are invisible, but not necessarily considered whitespace, which can lead to numerous issues.\r\nVim already has a mechanism to handle this (listchars), but currently there is no option to highlight these characters.\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nThe character set for nbsp should also be displayed for these other invisible characters.",
